The Iranian President: If sanctions against Iran are lifted, there is hope for a nuclear agreement to be reached - Xinhua News
Xinhua News Agency, Tehran, December 11th (Reporters Gao Wencheng and Wang Shoubo): Iranian President Lehi said on the 11th in the Iranian capital of Tehran, if the United States lifts sanctions on Iran, comprehensive negotiations on Iran's nuclear issue can reach a "good agreement".
According to a message released by the Iranian President's website, Lachii said in a meeting with the Iranian ambassadors to the neighboring countries that Iran has showed its willingness to negotiate by submitting a proposal to the other relevant parties to the Iranian nuclear agreement.
If the US side sets a strong determination, "the path to reach an agreement will be smooth."
The parties related to the Iranian nuclear agreement began talks in the Austrian capital Vienna in April of this year to discuss the restoration of the US-Iranian agreement.
The new round of talks will start in Vienna on November 29th and will adjourn temporarily on December 3rd, continuing on the 9th.
